.TH "fscrypt_drop_inode" 9 "fscrypt_drop_inode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fscrypt_drop_inode \- check whether the inode's master key has been removed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fscrypt_drop_inode
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
an inode being considered for eviction
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Filesystems supporting fscrypt must call this from their ->\fBdrop_inode\fP
method so that encrypted inodes are evicted as soon as they're no longer in
use and their master key has been removed.
.SH "RETURN"
1 if fscrypt wants the inode to be evicted now, otherwise 0
